<br>
Fricka took her seat behind the dark, Halas-wood desk, and continued writing.</font><P><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Elegant_Rogue/shanks/teenyknot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 11/4/00 6:37:16 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#a8a8a8><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufwank.showPublicProfile>fwank</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5/31/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>6:00:28 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Roleplay -- Allies?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The sage hit the fire with a puff of smoke, then flame... his hand reached to his side and grabbed the durfinite crystal, the one that was given to him before he could remember, by a shaman of great power.  That shaman had used this same crystal in a fire similar to this one long ago. . .that vision had predicted the war of the tribes that caused the current infection of the lands.  The Elder had been Fwanks spiritual guide, and he had died at the hands of the furry little ones.<br>
